# This directory holds update scripts that run on-demand (not automatically)
# Unlike startup.d (which runs on every login), update.d scripts are:
# - Prompted periodically (like oh-my-zsh updates)
# - Run manually via: bin/run-updates.sh
# - Potentially risky operations that shouldn't run automatically
#
# Examples of update.d scripts:
# - Homebrew updates
# - Git repo pulls
# - Package manager updates
